Golden Rule
Whenever the question says
same letters
rearrangement
permutation
grouping similar words
substring with same characters
frequency comparison
It is the category of Anagram
Approaches to Solve Anagram Problems
There are mainly 3 approaches.
Approach 1 : Sorting
Example
listen
silent
Sort both strings
eilnst
eilnst
Equal? Yes
Hence anagram.
Algorithm
Sort string1
Sort string2

Compare both the strings-

If equal
    Anagram

Else
    Not anagram
Complexity
Sorting

O(n log n)
Approach 2 : Frequency Array -
It works when only lowercase letters exist.
Example
listen
silent
Frequency array
int freq[26]   // [0,0,0,0,.....0]]
Step 1
Increase frequency of first string
listen

l++

i++

s++

t++

e++

n++
Frequency
a 0
b 0
...
e 1
i 1
l 1
n 1
s 1
t 1
Now decrease using second string
silent

s--

i--

l--

e--

n--

t--
Everything becomes 0 at the end
Therefore it is an Anagram.
Algorithm
For first string

freq[ch-'a']++

For second string

freq[ch-'a']--

If any frequency !=0

Not anagram

Else

Anagram
Complexity
Time

O(n)
